author: dfraser
title: Zlatan Ibrahimovic, Lionel Messi, Alexis Sanchez… None of these big names come close to Europe’s top shooter
text:
Zlatan Ibrahimovic comes in second in the shots taken this season standings 
The Dane's 88 shots have seen just five goals. 
Meanwhile, in second, United star Zlatan Ibrahimovic has taken 95 shots, with 39 on target and an impressive 15 goals. 
However, in first place, above all of those big-name stars... Roma's Edin Dzeko . Gabriel Jesus gets winner for Manchester City against Swansea Reuters Edin Dzeko has taken more shots than any other player in Europe this season 
The ex-City striker has taken a whopping 113 goals, with 52 of those hitting the target. 
Much like Zlatan, Sanchez and Icardi, he too has only scored 15 goals. 
With Gabriel Jesus keeping even Sergio Aguero out of the team however, it's fair to say City don't miss Bosnian ace Dzeko all that much.
